{"parse":{"title":"headphones","pageid":39979,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Audio-Technica ATH-A500 (2).jpg|thumb|right|pair of circumaural '''headphones''']]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|en|:af|head|phones|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɛdfəʊnz/|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-headphones.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɛdfoʊnz/|a=US}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Aadenboy-headphones.wav|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhedfəʉnz/|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhedfɐʉnz/|a=NZ}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɛdfonz/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈhɛdfoːnz/|a=Wales,non-toe-tow}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|p|sg=headphone}}\n\n# A pair of cushioned [[speaker]]s worn over or in the ears so only the wearer can hear the sound.\n#: {{syn|en|[[cans]] {{q|slang}}|heads}}\n#: {{ux|en|Circumaural '''headphones''' enclose the ear, supra-aural headphones rest on the ear's surface, and earbuds are placed inside the ear.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1995|artist=w:Björk|album={{w|Post (Björk album)|Post}}|title=Headphones|passage=My '''headphones''' / They saved my life / Your tape / It lulled me to sleep}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2005|author=Richard Corliss|title=Time|sectionurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070320075242/http://www.time.com/time/printout/0,8816,1013198,00.html|section=Profile of A.R. Rahman\n|passage=Toward the end of the film Nazu rushes into her bedroom, clamps on '''headphones''' and listens to the technopoppy \"I Wanna Be Free.\" The picturization shows her moving convulsively, desperately to the funky beat, turning ever more agitated, until we wonder what she wants to be free from: free from her domestic vise, or free from life?}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Alexandra Marvar|title=The New Detectorists|work=w:The New York Times|date=2021-05-31|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/05/31/style/metal-detectorists-ring-finders.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Detectorists may also carry '''headphones''', a metal detecting shovel, hand tools such as a hori-hori (a serrated, steel hand shovel), a “finds pouch,” and a hand-held precision detector called a pinpointer.}}\n## {{lb|en|specifically}} A pair of cushioned [[speaker]]s worn over or on the ears. \n##: {{ant|en|earphones|earbuds}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|pair of speakers worn over or in the ears so only the wearer can hear the sound}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|kufje|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|سَمَّاعَة|f}}, {{t|ar|سَمَاعَات الرَّأْس|f-p}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|ականջակալ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|qulaqlıq}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|наву́шнікі|f-p}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|слу́шалки|f-p}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|နားကြပ်}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|auriculars|m-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|耳機}}, {{t|cmn|耳筒}}\n* Czech: {{t|cs|sluchátka|n-p}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|hovedtelefoner|p}}, {{t|da|høretelefoner|p}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|hoofdtelefoon|m}}, {{t+|nl|koptelefoon|m}}\n* Elfdalian: {{t|ovd|ärlur|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|aŭskultiloj}}, {{t|eo|kapaŭskultiloj}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kõrvaklapid}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|oyralurtitól|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kuulokkeet}}, {{t|fi|luurit|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|casque|m}}, {{t+|fr|écouteurs|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Kopfhörer|m-p}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ακουστικά|n-p}}\n* Greenlandic: {{t|kl|naalaarutit siutaasat|p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|אוזניות|alt=אָזְנִית / אוזניות}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|आकर्णक|m}}, {{t|hi|हेडफ़ोन|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|fejhallgató}}, {{t+|hu|fülhallgató}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|heyrnartól|n}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|cluasáin|m-p}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|cuffie|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|ヘッドフォン|tr=heddofon}}, {{t+|ja|ヘッドホン|tr=heddohon}}, {{t+|ja|イヤフォン|tr=iyafon}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|құлаққап}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|កាស}} {{qualifier|French \"casque\"}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|헤드폰}}, {{t|ko|이어폰}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t|ky|кулаккап}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ຫູຟັງ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|auscultābulum|n}} {{q|New Latin}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|austiņas}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|Casque|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|слушалки|f-p}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|fon kepala}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|чихэвч}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{t|mn|ᠴᠢᠬᠢᠪᠴᠢ}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|hodetelefoner|p}}, {{t|nb|høretelefoner|p}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|hovudtelefonar|p}}, {{t|nn|høyretelefonar|p}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|слухалка|alt=слухалки}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|هدفون|tr=hedfon}}, {{t+|fa|گوشی|tr=guši}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|słuchawka|alt=słuchawki|nv-p}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|fones|m-p}}, {{t|pt|fones de cabeça|m-p}}, {{t|pt|auscultadores|m-p}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|cască|f}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|ureglier|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|нау́шники|m-p}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|oaivetelefovdna}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|слушалице|p}}\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|slušalice|p}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|හෙඩ්ෆෝන්}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|slúchadlá|p}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|slušalke|f-p}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{t|hsb|słuchatko|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|cascos|m-p}}, {{t+|es|auriculares|m-p}}, {{t+|es|audífonos|m-p}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hörlurar|c-p}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|หูฟัง}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|kulaklık}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|наву́шники|m-p}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|naushnik}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|ống nghe}}, {{t+|vi|tai nghe}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|clustffonau}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|en|headphone}}\n* {{l|en|earbud}}\n* {{l|en|earphones}}\n* {{l|en|earpiece}}\n* {{l|en|headset}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia|Headphones (disambiguation)}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n{{C|en|Headwear}}"}}